# Same idea as .gitignore, but for the image: things NOT to copy into the box.
# Everything you leave out makes the box smaller, faster, and safer.

# SECRETS — never bake config into an image. The box gets its config handed
# to it at startup from outside. This is THE rule.
.env

# Built on the host, for the host. Windows venv would break inside Linux.
# uv sync rebuilds it correctly inside the box.
.venv/

# Git history — the box needs the code, not the story of how it got here.
.git/
.gitignore

# Instruction sheet for running boxes. Useless INSIDE a box; nobody reads it there.
docker-compose.yml

# CI config — runs on GitHub, not in the box.
.github/

# Python litter
__pycache__/
*.py[oc]

# Celery Beat's local schedule file — the box makes its own.
celerybeat-schedule*

# Personal teaching notes — not part of the app.
CLAUDE.md
NOTES_*.md
